# Code of Conduct

## Our Commitment

The SDRM project is committed to providing a welcoming and respectful environment for everyone.

We encourage collaboration among researchers, engineers, and contributors from diverse backgrounds.

## Expected Behavior

Participants in the SDRM project should:

- Be respectful and professional
- Provide constructive feedback
- Support collaborative problem solving
- Respect different perspectives and expertise

## Unacceptable Behavior

The following behavior is not acceptable:

- Harassment or discrimination
- Personal attacks
- Disruptive or hostile conduct
- Publishing private information without permission

## Enforcement

Project maintainers may remove or restrict contributions that violate this code of conduct.

## Reporting Issues

If you experience or observe behavior that violates this code of conduct, please report it to:

sdrm.systems@gmail.com
